# Insecur Cursor Protocol

Follow the shared repo protocol. Do not create a Cursor-only workflow. Workflow logic lives in the
shared `ziw-*` skills under `skills/*/SKILL.md`; repo-specific workflow values live in
`docs/agents/workflow/config.md`.

Read these before implementation work:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/agents/workflow/config.md`
- `CONTEXT-MAP.md`
- `docs/agents/repo-navigation.md`
- the relevant `skills/*/SKILL.md` (`ziw-implement` for implementation work)
- the Linear issue body and linked context docs

Use `docs/agents/repo-navigation.md` to find the current status doc, package owner, local context
file, and spec before broad searching.

Implement one Linear issue per branch and PR per `ziw-implement`; startable-work criteria, branch
and PR conventions, and Linear state handling come from the config. Before opening a PR, run or
request `skills/ziw-code-review/SKILL.md` on the branch when the environment supports it, and
address blocking findings before PR handoff.

When the orchestrator sends `Changes Requested` feedback, continue in the same thread, branch, and
PR. Read the PR review comments, push fixes to the same PR, and move the issue back to `In Review`
when ready.

Stop and comment in Linear when product scope, security posture, credentials, provider approval, or
ADR decisions are missing.
